  {
    "id": "ce2016-q004",
    "type": "mcq",
    "topic": "data-structures-algorithms",
    "subtopic": "asymptotic-complexity",
    "stem": "The time complexity O(2000n – 1) can be represented by _________ .",
    "options": [
      {
        "label": "A",
        "text": "O(n)",
        "isCorrect": true
      },
      {
        "label": "B",
        "text": "O(1)",
        "isCorrect": false
      },
      {
        "label": "C",
        "text": "O(2000n)",
        "isCorrect": false
      },
      {
        "label": "D",
        "text": "O(2000)",
        "isCorrect": false
      }
    ],
    "answerOptionLabels": [
      "A"
    ],
    "explanation": "Big-O drops constant factors and lower-order terms, so O(2000n - 1) = O(n). The trap is answering O(2000n), which is not wrong mathematically but is not the reduced form Big-O asks for; the 2000 is a constant multiplier and the -1 is lower order.",
    "source": {
      "file": "[CE] questions.pdf",
      "exam": "K-Companies",
      "year": 2016,
      "tier": "gold",
      "originalNumber": 4
    },
