  {
    "id": "ce2016-q007",
    "type": "mcq",
    "topic": "data-structures-algorithms",
    "subtopic": "recurrence-relations",
    "stem": "If the function F(n) is as follows:\n\nWhat is the recurrence equation for the above algorithm?",
    "stemCode": "if(n<20)\n       return n;\nelse\n       return f(n-2)+f(n-1);",
    "options": [
      {
        "label": "A",
        "text": "T(n-2)+T(n-1)+n",
        "isCorrect": false
      },
      {
        "label": "B",
        "text": "T(n-2)+T(n-1)-n",
        "isCorrect": false
      },
      {
        "label": "C",
        "text": "T(n-2)+T(n-1)+1",
        "isCorrect": true
      },
      {
        "label": "D",
        "text": "T(n-2)+T(n-1)",
        "isCorrect": false
      }
    ],
    "answerOptionLabels": [
      "C"
    ],
    "explanation": "The function makes two recursive calls, on n-1 and n-2, and does only constant work per call (one comparison plus one addition), so T(n) = T(n-2) + T(n-1) + 1. The trap is choosing the +n version, which would apply only if the body did O(n) work such as a loop over n; here the body is O(1).",
    "source": {
      "file": "[CE] questions.pdf",
      "exam": "K-Companies",
      "year": 2016,
      "tier": "gold",
      "originalNumber": 7
    },
    "keyProvenance": "answer_page",
