  {
    "id": "ce2016-q013",
    "type": "mcq",
    "topic": "digital-logic",
    "subtopic": "boolean-simplification",
    "stem": "The function xy + xy' is minimized to __________ .",
    "options": [
      {
        "label": "A",
        "text": "x",
        "isCorrect": true
      },
      {
        "label": "B",
        "text": "x + y'",
        "isCorrect": false
      },
      {
        "label": "C",
        "text": "x + y",
        "isCorrect": false
      },
      {
        "label": "D",
        "text": "y'",
        "isCorrect": false
      }
    ],
    "answerOptionLabels": [
      "A"
    ],
    "explanation": "Factor out x: xy + xy' = x(y + y'), and y + y' = 1 by the complement law, so the result is x·1 = x. The distractors come from misapplying distribution: adding rather than factoring gives the bogus x + y or x + y'.",
    "source": {
      "file": "[CE] questions.pdf",
      "exam": "K-Companies",
      "year": 2016,
      "tier": "gold",
      "originalNumber": 13
    },
    "keyProvenance": "answer_page",
    "keyVerified": true,
    "verificationLevel": "double",
    "needsReview": false,
    "flags": [],
    "dedupeHash": "5c41583bc56dd573f8a5893725b495c06a98da1e"
  },
  {
    "id": "ce2016-q014",
    "type": "mcq",
    "topic": "operating-systems",
    "subtopic": "cpu-scheduling",
    "stem": "Round Robin is essentially the preemptive a version of ___________ .",
    "options": [
      {
        "label": "A",
        "text": "SJF (Shortest Job First)",
        "isCorrect": false
      },
      {
        "label": "B",
        "text": "FIFO",
        "isCorrect": true
      },
      {
        "label": "C",
        "text": "LIFO",
        "isCorrect": false
      },
      {
        "label": "D",
        "text": "Longest Time First.",
        "isCorrect": false
      }
    ],
    "answerOptionLabels": [
      "B"
    ],
    "explanation": "Round Robin is FIFO (FCFS) with a time quantum bolted on: processes are dispatched in arrival order from a FIFO ready queue, but a process that exhausts its quantum is preempted and put back at the tail. SJF is the trap, its preemptive version is SRTF (Shortest Remaining Time First), not Round Robin.",
    "source": {
      "file": "[CE] questions.pdf",
      "exam": "K-Companies",
      "year": 2016,
      "tier": "gold",
      "originalNumber": 14
    },
    "keyProvenance": "answer_page",
    "keyVerified": true,
    "verificationLevel": "double",
    "needsReview": false,
    "flags": [],
    "dedupeHash": "a77e8e13cb82cad640060658216224244c4efad7"
  },
  {
    "id": "ce2016-q015",
    "type": "true_false",
    "topic": "data-structures-algorithms",
    "subtopic": "binary-trees",
    "stem": "In a balanced binary tree, the left and right subtree has the same number of nodes.",
    "options": [
      {
        "label": "A",
        "text": "True",
        "isCorrect": false
      },
      {
        "label": "B",
        "text": "False",
        "isCorrect": true
      }
    ],
    "answerOptionLabels": [
      "B"
    ],
    "explanation": "False. Balanced refers to HEIGHT, not node count: a tree is height-balanced when the heights of the left and right subtrees differ by at most 1 at every node. A balanced tree can easily have 3 nodes on one side and 1 on the other, so equal node counts is not required.",
    "source": {
      "file": "[CE] questions.pdf",
      "exam": "K-Companies",
      "year": 2016,
      "tier": "gold",
      "originalNumber": 15
