  {
    "id": "ce2016-q017",
    "type": "mcq",
    "topic": "networking",
    "subtopic": "network-devices",
    "stem": "What is the function of a Network Bridge?",
    "options": [
      {
        "label": "A",
        "text": "Connect two nodes in the same network.",
        "isCorrect": false
      },
      {
        "label": "B",
        "text": "Connect two LANs.",
        "isCorrect": true
      },
      {
        "label": "C",
        "text": "Control Network Speed.",
        "isCorrect": false
      },
      {
        "label": "D",
        "text": "None of the above.",
        "isCorrect": false
      }
    ],
    "answerOptionLabels": [
      "B"
    ],
    "explanation": "A bridge is a data-link (layer 2) device that joins two LANs or LAN segments into one logical network and forwards or filters frames based on MAC addresses. Option A describes cabling within one segment, not a bridge, and C describes traffic shaping, which no bridge does.",
    "source": {
      "file": "[CE] questions.pdf",
      "exam": "K-Companies",
      "year": 2016,
      "tier": "gold",
      "originalNumber": 17
    },
